  "text": "Using a variety of biochemical approaches, Tchesnokov et al. [CITATION_1] found evidence that HIV-1 might exploit two pathways to resistance to acyclovir [CITATION_2] , an anti-herpes agent with activity against HIV-1 [CITATION_3] . Earlier work showed that acyclovir selects for HIV-1 RT mutations V75I, M184V and T69N, with V75I as the dominant mutation [CITATION_4] .",
